FINAL SUMMARY
======================================================================

Dataset: 417 wild Entiat steelhead across 20 return years
  Group A (Rocky Reach only, no Wells): 223 fish
  Group B (Wells interaction, non-stray): 181 fish
  Excluded strays (last in Methow/Okanogan): 13 fish

Entiat River detection rates:
  Group A: 89.7% (200/223)
  Group B: 68.0% (123/181)

MODEL 1 — Wells Interaction Effect (all fish, year random effect):
  beta_wells = -1.394 (95% HDI: [-1.950, -0.882])
  Odds Ratio = 0.248
  P(Wells DECREASES Entiat return) = 1.0000

  beta_harvest = -0.306 (95% HDI: [-1.271, 0.592])
  Odds Ratio = 0.736
  P(harvest open increases return) = 0.2599

MODEL 1b — Wells Effect After Controlling for Spring Return Season:
  beta_wells = -1.402 (95% HDI: [-1.939, -0.882])
  Odds Ratio = 0.246
  P(Wells DECREASES Entiat return) = 1.0000
  [Robustness check: effect should persist after accounting for
   lower spring detection efficiency]
MODEL 2 — Spill at Wells Predicting Group B Entiat Return:
  Spring Spill Hours: beta=0.063, OR=1.066, P(>0)=0.601
  Fall Spill Hours:   beta=-0.045, OR=0.956, P(>0)=0.412
  Harvest Open:       beta=0.122, OR=1.130, P(>0)=0.606
  [None of the spill/harvest metrics predict within-group variation]

